HEADWORD: Dirempt
<hw>Di*rempt"</hw> <pr>(?; 215)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>diremptus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>dirimere</ets> to take apart,
separate; <ets>di- = dis-</ets> + <ets>emere</ets> to buy, orig., to
take.]</ety> <def>Divided; separated.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Stow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Dirempt</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Dirempt
<hw>Di*rempt"</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <def>To separate by force; to tear
apart.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Holinshed.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

